Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - Abstract Although reserve requirements (RR) have been used in emerging markets to smooth credit cycles, the transmission mechanism remains blurry. Using bank-level data, we unveil the interaction of RR with bank lending. We identify a new channel that works through a decline in banks? liquid assets and loan supply due to an increase in RR. ?Quantitative tightening? through RR raises the short-term funding needs of the banking system, which is met by collateralized central bank lending, thus depleting banks? unencumbered liquid assets. Our results suggest that such a shift in bank liquidity is associated with a significant change in lending.
ER  - 

